        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40830",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=erickwilder",
                        "name": "erickwilder",
                        "displayName": "Erick Wilder de Oliveira",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Not sure if is really necessary to extend a Writer. Just setting a Formatter to the current Writer doesn't does the trick?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=erickwilder",
                        "name": "erickwilder",
                        "displayName": "Erick Wilder de Oliveira",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-06-02T05:45:54.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-06-02T05:45:54.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41078",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ashawley",
                        "name": "ashawley",
                        "displayName": "Aaron S. Hawley",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Here's a patch against 1.10.4 that simply duplicates the way writers and filters are generated as application resources.\r\n\r\nI tested only:\r\n\r\n{noformat}\r\nresources.log.db.formatterName = \"Simple\"\r\nresources.log.db.formatterParams.format = '%timestamp%: %message%'\r\n{noformat}\r\n\r\nNot the testing of Namespace.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ashawley",
                        "name": "ashawley",
                        "displayName": "Aaron S. Hawley",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-06-18T14:26:31.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-06-18T14:26:31.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43869",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=intiilapa",
                        "name": "intiilapa",
                        "displayName": "Beno\u00eet Durand",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "r23599",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=intiilapa",
                        "name": "intiilapa",
                        "displayName": "Beno\u00eet Durand",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-30T09:54:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-30T09:54:02.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43895",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ashawley",
                        "name": "ashawley",
                        "displayName": "Aaron S. Hawley",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Benoit, thanks for taking this on.\r\n\r\nPerhaps, this should be added to the existing tests for Zend_Application_Resource_Log?\r\n\r\n{noformat}\r\nIndex: trunk\/tests\/Zend\/Application\/Resource\/LogTest.php\r\n===================================================================\r\n--- trunk\/tests\/Zend\/Application\/Resource\/LogTest.php\t(revision 23599)\r\n+++ trunk\/tests\/Zend\/Application\/Resource\/LogTest.php\t(working copy)\r\n@@ -109,5 +109,13 @@\r\n             'writerParams' => array(\r\n                 'stream' => $stream,\r\n-            )\r\n+            ),\r\n+            'filterName'   => 'Priority',\r\n+            'filterParams' => array(\r\n+                'priority' => Zend_Log::INFO,\r\n+            ),\r\n+            'formatterName'   => 'Simple',\r\n+            'formatterParams' => array(\r\n+                'format' => '%timestamp%: %message%',\r\n+            ),\r\n         ));\r\n \r\n@@ -121,5 +129,7 @@\r\n         $log->log($message = 'logged-message', Zend_Log::INFO);\r\n         rewind($stream);\r\n-        $this->assertContains($message, stream_get_contents($stream));\r\n+        $contents = stream_get_contents($stream);\r\n+        $this->assertStringEndsWith($message, $contents);\r\n+        $this->assertRegexp('\/\\d\\d:\\d\\d:\\d\\d\/', $contents);\r\n     }\r\n{noformat}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ashawley",
                        "name": "ashawley",
                        "displayName": "Aaron S. Hawley",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-01-03T08:53:58.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-01-03T08:53:58.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43906",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Benoit -- patch looks good, but I also think Aaron's point is valid. Once the Log resource test is added, feel free to merge to the 1.11 release branch.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-01-04T06:04:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-01-04T06:04:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44134",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=intiilapa",
                        "name": "intiilapa",
                        "displayName": "Beno\u00eet Durand",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I have committed the unit test of Aaron in the trunk r23642. And, I added documentation in r23675.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=intiilapa",
                        "name": "intiilapa",
                        "displayName": "Beno\u00eet Durand",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-01-23T01:16:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-01-23T12:03:46.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44332",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=neofraktal",
                        "name": "neofraktal",
                        "displayName": "Alberto",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Documentation appears as:\r\n\r\nfilterParams -> format\r\n\r\nbut you must to use:\r\n\r\nformatterParams -> format\r\n\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=neofraktal",
                        "name": "neofraktal",
                        "displayName": "Alberto",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-02-10T00:48:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-02-10T00:48:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48427",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fr0z3nk0",
                        "name": "fr0z3nk0",
                        "displayName": "Peter Culak",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm using tag http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/svn\/framework\/standard\/tags\/release-1.11.7\/library\/Zend.\r\nthis setting in application.ini just gets ignored:\r\nresources.log.stream.formatterNamespace = \"Model_Log_Formatter\"\r\n\r\nthe reason for it is that Zend_Log calls this on line 225:\r\n$formatter = $this->_constructFromConfig('formatter', $config, $this->_defaultFormatterNamespace);\r\n\r\nhas this fix not been included in release yet ?\r\n\r\npeter",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fr0z3nk0",
                        "name": "fr0z3nk0",
                        "displayName": "Peter Culak",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-09-14T12:56:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-09-14T12:56:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48429",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=intiilapa",
                        "name": "intiilapa",
                        "displayName": "Beno\u00eet Durand",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "What fix are you talking about?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=intiilapa",
                        "name": "intiilapa",
                        "displayName": "Beno\u00eet Durand",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-09-14T18:31:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-09-14T18:31:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48440",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fr0z3nk0",
                        "name": "fr0z3nk0",
                        "displayName": "Peter Culak",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "fix which would allow to set a namespace from through config file. the patch attached above doesn't allow that as it does: \r\nprotected function _constructFormatterFromConfig($config)\r\n+    {\r\n+        $formatter = $this->_constructFromConfig('formatter', $config, $this->_defaultFormatterNamespace);\r\n\r\n$this->_defaultFormatterNamespace should probably pick up formatterNamespace from config first and if not set then use default one.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fr0z3nk0",
                        "name": "fr0z3nk0",
                        "displayName": "Peter Culak",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-09-15T08:56:25.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-09-15T08:56:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48447",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=intiilapa",
                        "name": "intiilapa",
                        "displayName": "Beno\u00eet Durand",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This feature is added since version 1.11.3. Would you have a sample of a configuration that does not work?\r\n\r\nYou make a misreading of the source code. You should read the *getClassName* method: a default namespace is used only if the configuration does not provide to complete the short name.\r\n{code:title=\"Zend_Log::getClassName()\"}\r\n        \/\/ line 295\r\n        $namespace = $defaultNamespace;\r\n        if (isset($config[ $type . 'Namespace' ])) {\r\n            $namespace = $config[ $type . 'Namespace' ];\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        $fullClassName = $namespace . '_' . $className;\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nYou should open a new issue as bug to discuss if there really is a bug on this feature.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=intiilapa",
                        "name": "intiilapa",
                        "displayName": "Beno\u00eet Durand",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-09-15T17:43:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-09-15T17:45:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48463",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fr0z3nk0",
                        "name": "fr0z3nk0",
                        "displayName": "Peter Culak",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "you're right, it works fine. I was extending formatter and i didn't overload factory method so it was returning wrong class.\r\n\r\nthanx for your time ;)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fr0z3nk0",
                        "name": "fr0z3nk0",
                        "displayName": "Peter Culak",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-09-19T13:24:33.000+0000",
